  • Method Details

    • Alerts

      public static void Alerts(String alertType)
      Method for notification alerts throughout the program. Lambda expressions are used here for brevity of code and because the expression contains no additional arguments. Here the lambdas refer to variables from their enclosing scope i.e (the string switch Strings), those variables are captured, so I can refer to them when applying a lambda later. I do not refer to these variables outside the current method.

    • exitHere

      public static void exitHere()
      Method to exit the program. I used a lambda expression here for brevity of code, but also to show how further arguments can be included if wrapped in brackets. This is the same syntax for lambda expressions for all the "show and Wait" alerts in the program. The Lambda here is used as a shorthand for writing a class to implement a functional interface and then instantiating that class.
